# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in. Bun auto-loads .env at daemon startup.
#
# AI (Smart Commit + AI commit messages) is bring-your-own-key: add your key in the app under
# Settings → AI. There's no bundled key — Groq revokes any key committed to a public repo, so a
# shipped one is dead on arrival. Groq is the suggested provider (free + fast, ~30s):
#   https://console.groq.com/keys
#
# No environment variables are required to run RepoYeti.
